<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><entry xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="entry_dy" xml:lang="os"><form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>dy</orth></form><form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>du</orth></form><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>ты</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>thou</q></cit></sense><cit type="exampleGroup" corresp="#sense_dy." n=""><cit type="example"><quote>bazon ma sæ dy!</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>узнай-ка их ты!</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>you recognize them!</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>105</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example"><quote>du min k˳ʽ waisæ kʼoxbælxwæcægæm...</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>если бы ты был мне за шафера...</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>if you were my best man...</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_ОЭп."/><biblScope>58%l148%l</biblScope></bibl></cit></cit><cit type="exampleGroup" corresp="#sense_." n=""><cit type="example"><quote>bazon ma sæ dy!</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>узнай-ка их ты!</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>you recognize them!</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>105</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example"><quote>du min k˳ʽ waisæ kʼoxbælxwæcægæm...</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>если бы ты был мне за шафера...</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>if you were my best man...</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_ОЭп."/><biblScope>58%l148%l</biblScope></bibl></cit></cit><etym xml:lang="ru">Общеиндоевропейское личное местоимение. Восходит к *%itu%i. Редкий случай, где %it%i в начальном положении перешел в %id%i (ср. <xr><ref target="#entry_dasyn"/></xr> ‘брить’). Аналогичное явление в армянском (ср.: <bibl corresp="#ref_Brugmann"><biblScope>II 767</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl corresp="#ref_Hübschmann._Arm._Gr."><biblScope>440</biblScope></bibl>). Какие причины вызвали этот необычайный перебой в <mentioned xml:lang="os"><lang/><w>du</w></mentioned> — неясно. Можно высказать догадку, что озвончение имело место сперва в энклитических формах <mentioned xml:lang="os"><lang/><w>dæ</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="os"><w>dæm</w></mentioned>,  и пр., так как они в потоке речи очень часто попадали в положение, необходимо влекущее озвончение (после гласных, сонорных и звонких согласных). Ср. в афганском энклитическую форму <mentioned xml:lang="ps"><lang/><w>de</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ps"><w>di</w></mentioned>,  при <mentioned xml:lang="ps"><lang/><w>tə</w><gloss><q>ты</q></gloss></mentioned>. Со временем %id%i из энклитических форм был перенесен и на самостоятельное %idu%i. Соответствия в иранских и индоевропейских языках: <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>tu</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ku"><lang/><w>tu</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ps"><lang/><w>tə</w></mentioned> (энкл. <mentioned xml:lang="ps"><lang/><w>de</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ps"><w>di</w></mentioned>, ), <mentioned xml:lang=""><lang/><w>tu</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang=""><w>tə</w></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="yai"><lang/><w>tu</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/><w>thu</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/><w>tū</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ae"><w>tūm</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><w>tvām</w></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="peo"><lang/><w>tuvam</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/><w>tvam</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="xcl"><lang/><w>du</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="cu"><lang/><w>ты</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/><w>ты</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="lt"><lang/><w>tù</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="got"><lang/><w>%bP%bu</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="de"><lang/><w>du</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><lang/><w>τύ</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="grc"><w>σύ</w></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/><w>tū</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sga"><lang/><w>tū</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="hit"><lang/><w>-du</w></mentioned>. Ср. <xr><ref target="#entry_dæ"/><ref target="#entry_dæw"/></xr>.%n<bibl corresp="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"><biblScope>II 78, 146—147</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl corresp="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."><biblScope>30, 51</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl corresp="#ref_Hübschmann._Oss."><biblScope>37</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl corresp="#ref_ОЯФ_I"><biblScope>22</biblScope></bibl>.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">A common Indo-European personal pronoun. It traces back to *%itu%i. A rare case when %it%i in the initial position turned into %id%i (cf. <xr><ref target="#entry_dasyn"/></xr> ‘shave’). A similar phenomenon is attested in Armenian (cf.: <bibl corresp="#ref_Brugmann"><biblScope>II 767</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl corresp="#ref_Hübschmann._Arm._Gr."><biblScope>440</biblScope></bibl>). It is unclear which reasons caused this unusual transition to <mentioned xml:lang="os"><lang/><w>du</w></mentioned>. One can guess that the voicing took place first in enclitic forms <mentioned xml:lang="os"><lang/><w>dæ</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="os"><w>dæm</w></mentioned>,  etc., since they used to very often get into a position necessarily causing the voicing process (after vowels, sonorants and voiced consonants). Cf. an enclitic form in Pashto <mentioned xml:lang="ps"><lang/><w>de</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ps"><w>di</w></mentioned>,  and <mentioned xml:lang="ps"><lang/><w>tə</w><gloss><q>you</q></gloss></mentioned>. Over time, %id%i was transferred to an independent form %idu%i from enclitic forms. Correspondences in Iranian and Indo-European languages are the following: <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>tu</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ku"><lang/><w>tu</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ps"><lang/><w>tə</w></mentioned> (encl. <mentioned xml:lang="ps"><lang/><w>de</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ps"><w>di</w></mentioned>, ), <mentioned xml:lang=""><lang/><w>tu</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang=""><w>tə</w></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="yai"><lang/><w>tu</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/><w>thu</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/><w>tū</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ae"><w>tūm</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><w>tvām</w></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="peo"><lang/><w>tuvam</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/><w>tvam</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="xcl"><lang/><w>du</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="cu"><lang/><w>ty</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/><w>ty</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="lt"><lang/><w>tù</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="got"><lang/><w>%bP%bu</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="de"><lang/><w>du</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><lang/><w>τύ</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="grc"><w>σύ</w></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/><w>tū</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sga"><lang/><w>tū</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="hit"><lang/><w>-du</w></mentioned>. Cf. <xr><ref target="#entry_dæ"/><ref target="#entry_dæw"/></xr>.%n<bibl corresp="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"><biblScope>II 78, 146—147</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl corresp="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."><biblScope>30, 51</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl corresp="#ref_Hübschmann._Oss."><biblScope>37</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl corresp="#ref_ОЯФ_I"><biblScope>22</biblScope></bibl>.</etym></entry>